sec.p:
The high-level optimisation formulation used in DER-CAM follows the standard linear programming approach
(1)minf=cT·x=(c1…cn)T·(x1…xn)=c1·x1+…+cn·xns.t.Ax≤bL≤x≤U
where

c
is the cost coefficient vector;
x,
the decision variable vector;
A,
the constraint coefficient matrix;
b,
the constraint coefficient vector;
L,
the decision variable lower boundary vector;
U,
the decision variable upper boundary vector.
